Scope
1. End-to-End Runtime Verification

Validate the complete lifecycle:

Create Module
Create Business Entity
Add Fields
Design Views
Publish
Runtime Registration
Navigation Generation
Generated Grid
Generated Form
Create/Edit/Delete Record
2. Navigation Review

Confirm:

Dynamic sidebar
Module grouping
Ordering
Icons
Breadcrumbs
Deep linking
3. Runtime Routing

Verify:

/runtime/{module}/{entity}
/runtime/{module}/{entity}/new
/runtime/{module}/{entity}/{id}

No hardcoded routes.

4. Dynamic Forms

Verify:

Required fields
Default values
Read-only fields
Hidden fields
Validation
Save
Cancel
Error handling
5. Dynamic Grids

Verify:

Sorting
Filtering
Search
Pagination
Export
Selection
Row actions
6. Runtime Manifest

Confirm that every published entity has a runtime descriptor consumed consistently by:

Navigation
Runtime UI
Search
Authorization
7. Runtime Cache

Validate:

Publish refreshes affected caches only.
No stale metadata.
No full cache rebuild unless required.
8. Security Review

Confirm:

Runtime pages enforce authorization.
Generated actions respect permissions.
Hidden actions are not callable directly.
9. Performance

Review:

Metadata loading
Manifest loading
Generated forms
Generated grids
Query efficiency
10. Error Handling

Ensure:

User-friendly validation
Structured logging
No unhandled runtime exceptions
11. Production Readiness

Verify:

No TODOs
No placeholder code
No mock implementations
TypeScript clean
No new lint issues
Runtime stable
Exit Criteria

VS06R is complete when an administrator can:

Create a Platform Module.
Create a Business Entity.
Define Fields.
Design Views.
Publish the entity.
See it appear automatically in the navigation.
Open the generated runtime page.
Create, edit, and delete records.
Observe correct authorization, audit, and runtime behavior.

At that point, the Metadata Platform (CM-001 Milestone 1) can be considered functionally complete.